body_html:
Bazel protobuf is not empty. Ive listed the output here

flavia@fninsiima-ThinkPad-T440p:~/Documents/tensorflow/bazel-tensorflow/external/protobuf$ ls
appveyor.bat generate_descriptor_proto.sh protobuf-lite.pc.in
appveyor.yml gmock.BUILD protobuf.pc.in
autogen.sh java Protobuf.podspec
benchmarks javanano protoc-artifacts
BUILD jenkins python
CHANGES.txt js README.md
cmake LICENSE ruby
configure.ac m4 six.BUILD
conformance Makefile.am src
CONTRIBUTORS.txt more_tests tests.sh
csharp objectivec update_file_lists.sh
docs php util
editors post_process_dist.sh WORKSPACE
examples protobuf.bzl

Yes, ive verified that arm-linux-androideabi-gcc exists on my system.
But I'm not sure how to verify that its executable...

On opening it(double clicking), it says

'There is no application installed for “executable” files.'

On doing so in terminal, it says

The program 'arm-linux-androideabi-gcc' is currently not installed. You can install it by typing:

sudo apt-get install gcc-arm-linux-androideabi

No, i do not recall cloning with --recurse-submodules.
